radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 10 mm in diameter with an enhancing wall, intraluminal fluid, and slight surrounding fat stranding. The lung bases appear clear. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands appear within normal limits. The stomach, small and large bowel appear within normal limits. The prostate, seminal vesicles, distal ureters, and bladder appear within normal range. The major mesenteric arteries and veins appear patent. There are no enlarged lymph nodes or ascites. There are no suspicious bone lesions and the vertebral body heights and disc spaces appear preserved.
